      "source": "## 2. Gaussian Peak Fitting [S+N]\n\nFitting a Gaussian profile $y = A \\exp\\!\\left(-\\frac{(x - \\mu)^2}{2\\sigma^2}\\right)$ to spectral or chromatographic data. Again, derive the gradient symbolically.",
